    <stitle>International&#174; T 444E Diesel Engine Service, Model Year 1994 - 1998 - MANIFOLDS - Inspection</stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>Inspection</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="inspect" graphiccount="1">
            <title>Exhaust Manifold</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Inspect the cleaned exhaust manifolds for cracks. Replace the exhaust manifold as
                    required.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1200306" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figeg2/eg2517.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="328px"
                         scalefitheight="392px" box="yes"/>
                <caption>Inspecting the Exhaust Manifold for Warp</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Exhaust Manifold</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Straight Edge</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Feeler Gauge</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">To inspect the exhaust manifold for warp , place a straight edge against the mounting
                    surface and try passing a 0.13 mm (0.005 in) feeler gauge between the straight edge and mounting
                    surface.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>If the feeler gauge passes through, the exhaust manifold requires a gasket. Attach a gasket to
                        the exhaust manifold and proceed to the installation procedure.
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>If a gasket was previously used on the exhaust manifold, the manifold may be machined to
                        compensate for warp. A maximum of 0.25 mm (0.010 in) material can be machined off to correct
                        warp.
                    </para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
